    "intro_html": "<p>White siding with a charcoal roof is a softer take on the iconic black-and-white formula - the contrast is still strong, but charcoal introduces enough gray warmth to prevent the elevation from reading as stark.</p><p>It suits modern farmhouse, coastal, and transitional styles equally well. White trim unifies the roofline with the body; warm wood or stone accents add depth. For homeowners who want the clean, high-contrast look but find pure black too severe, charcoal is the well-calibrated middle ground.</p>",
